+# Fix for Import Ordering Issue with Multiple Blank Line Separators
+
+## Issue Description
+
+When using the `ij_kotlin_imports_layout` configuration with multiple `|` (blank line) separators, ktlint version 0.48.2 was generating extra blank lines before the first import in a file. The number of extra blank lines corresponded to the number of `|` separators that appeared before the pattern matching the first import.
+
+### Example Configuration
+```
+ij_kotlin_imports_layout = *, |, javax.**, java.**, |, kotlinx.**, kotlin.**
+```
+
+### Expected Behavior
+For a file containing only `java.**` imports:
+```kotlin
+package test
+
+import java.nio.file.Files
+import java.nio.file.Paths
+import java.util.Objects
+
+object TestData {
+    // ...
+}
+```
+
+### Observed Behavior (Bug)
+```kotlin
+package test
+
+
+
+import java.nio.file.Files
+import java.nio.file.Paths
+import java.util.Objects
+
+object TestData {
+    // ...
+}
+```
+
+Note the extra blank lines between the package declaration and imports.
+
+## Root Cause
+
+In `ImportOrderingRule.kt`, the logic for inserting blank lines between import groups was checking ALL patterns from the beginning (index 0) up to the first import's pattern index when processing the first import (`prev == null`). This caused any blank line separators (`|`) that appeared before the first import's matching pattern to be incorrectly added before the first import.
+
+### Code Location
+File: `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/ImportOrderingRule.kt`
+
+Lines 76-96 (before fix):
+```kotlin
+sortedImports.fold(null as ASTNode?) { prev, current ->
+    val index1 = if (prev == null) -1 else importSorter.findImportIndex((prev.psi as KtImportDirective).importPath!!)
+    val index2 = importSorter.findImportIndex((current.psi as KtImportDirective).importPath!!)
+
+    var hasBlankLines = false
+    for (i in (index1 + 1) until index2) {  // When prev is null, this checks from 0 to index2
+        if (importSorter.patterns[i] == PatternEntry.BLANK_LINE_ENTRY) {
+            hasBlankLines = true
+            break
+        }
+    }
+    if (hasBlankLines) {
+        sortedImportsWithSpaces += PsiWhiteSpaceImpl("\n\n")  // Adds blank line BEFORE first import
+    }
+    sortedImportsWithSpaces += current
+
+    return@fold current
+}
+```
+
+## Solution
+
+Added a check to only look for blank line patterns when there is a previous import (`prev != null`). This ensures that blank lines are only inserted BETWEEN import groups, never before the first import.
+
+### Modified Code
+Lines 80-89 (after fix):
+```kotlin
+var hasBlankLines = false
+// Only check for blank lines between imports, not before the first import
+if (prev != null) {
+    for (i in (index1 + 1) until index2) {
+        if (importSorter.patterns[i] == PatternEntry.BLANK_LINE_ENTRY) {
+            hasBlankLines = true
+            break
+        }
+    }
+}
+```
+
+## Testing
+
+### New Test Files
+1. `ImportOrderingRuleIssueTest.kt` - Tests for the specific issue scenarios
+2. `ImportOrderingRuleRegressionTest.kt` - Comprehensive regression tests including:
+   - The exact scenario from the reported issue
+   - Multiple blank line separators before the first matching pattern
+   - Idempotency verification (running format twice should produce same result)
+   - Complex layouts with multiple groups
+
+### Test Results
+- All new tests pass ✓
+- All existing import ordering tests pass ✓
+- No regressions in the full test suite ✓
+
+## Impact
+
+This fix:
+1. Resolves the reported issue where multiple blank line separators caused extra blank lines before the first import
+2. Makes the import formatting idempotent (applying format twice produces the same result)
+3. Maintains backward compatibility with existing import layout configurations
+4. Does not affect the insertion of blank lines between import groups (which still works correctly)
+
+## Files Changed
+
+1. **ImportOrderingRule.kt** - Core fix (lines 81-89)
+2. **ImportOrderingRuleIssueTest.kt** - New test file
+3. **ImportOrderingRuleRegressionTest.kt** - New test file
+

